\description{
\code{sus_grid_pollution_ghap()} downloads, crops, spatially aggregates, and
caches GHAP (GlobalHighAirPollutants) raster data to Brazilian
municipalities. No API key is required.

GHAP provides AI-generated, seamless ground-level air pollutant fields at
1 km (PM2.5, CO) and 10 km (O3) resolution. Files are downloaded as NetCDF
from Zenodo, cropped to Brazil, aggregated with area-weighted extraction,
and the result is stored as a Parquet cache for fast subsequent access.

Available pollutants and temporal coverage:
\itemize{
\item \strong{PM2.5} (\code{"pm25"}) — daily, monthly & annual, 2017–2022, 1 km, \eqn{\mu g/m^3}
\item \strong{O3} (\code{"o3"}) — annual only, 2000–2020, 10 km, ppb
\item \strong{CO} (\code{"co"}) — annual only, 2019–2022, 1 km, mg/m\eqn{^3}
\item \strong{NO2} (\code{"no2"}) — data not yet publicly released
}

When \code{municipalities} is provided the function returns a \code{climasus_df} at
\code{stage = "climate"}, \code{type = "pollution_ghap"}, compatible with
\code{\link[=sus_climate_anomaly]{sus_climate_anomaly()}}, \code{\link[=sus_climate_aggregate]{sus_climate_aggregate()}}, and \code{\link[=sus_mod_dlnm]{sus_mod_dlnm()}}.
